If it goes through the entire loop without breaking, then it doesn't output anything? But wait: the first program has a condition in the loop: 
      if (c[i] == '1') {
          if (i == k-1) {
              System.out.println(1);
              return;
          }
      } else {
          System.out.println(c[i]);
          return;
      } So if at the i-th character (0-indexed) we have:
   - If it is '1' and we are at the last index (i = k-1), then we print 1 and return.
   - If it is not '1', we print that character and return.
